==Outside Oman==
The khanjar is not unique to Oman, and neither is the jembiya unique to Yemen. The words khanjar and jembiya are often interchangeable in Arabic so these two articles should be more inclusive. In South Asia, the word khanjar is more commonly associated with swords while a dagger is called khanjarli. [[User:Morinae|Morinae]] ([[User talk:Morinae|talk]]) 10:16, 15 July 2010 (UTC)
*Khanjar are a well know dagger in India, Persia and other countries, there are a lot of references both written and visual to back this up, the article needs to include this information if it is to be accurate and factual.[[Special:Contributions/70.196.131.82|70.196.131.82]] ([[User talk:70.196.131.82|talk]]) 08:24, 17 February 2015 (UTC)
